Dangote Fertilizer generated N30 billion in revenues and contributed 2.3% to Dangote Groupâ€™s revenue (as of 30 September 2021), as the first line of the project produced 347,000 tonnes of urea in 2021, according to data seen by MoneyCentral. Dangote Fertilizer comprises of two 4,000 tons per day (TPD) urea production lines, positioning the Dangote Group as a leading manufacturer of urea fertilizer globally. The second line commenced production of ammonia in February 2022, with stable production of urea expected to be achieved by end of May 2022. Ammonia production will be used in its entirety as feedstock for the Urea plant. -Advertisement- Dangote Fertilizer intends to sell 75% of its produce in international markets upon the commissioning of the second line having recorded 55% in export sales so far.